  "text": "Qualitatively, with the possible exception of the very coarse 16 2 simulation for Re = 10 000, all curves are strictly monotonically decreasing. This is in agreement with the theoretical considerations in Section 3. Indeed, equation [CITATION_1] predicts that the decrease in enstrophy is especially strong whenever the palinstrophy is high and, in anticipation of Figure 8 , this behavior is very well observable for Re ∈ {1000, 10 000}.",
